it's like you're trying to gain momentum with it, trying to establish it, et cetera. Like,

00:45:40.020 --> 00:45:44.979
have you had to come up with a different way to approach the Python community than maybe you would

00:45:44.979 --> 00:45:49.780
have taken for granted in our community? Like, we know that community has changed so much over

00:45:49.780 --> 00:45:55.379
15, 20 years. Like, what's it like to come into the Python community now? And how did that feel?

00:45:55.860 --> 00:45:59.860
What was successful? Was it hard? Curious how you come into that space.

